
msgid "Configuration"
msgstr ""

msgid "Configuration file"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"The key artifact that defines the ``tt`` environment and various aspects of "
"its execution is its configuration file."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"By default, the configuration file is called ``tt.yaml``. The location where"
" ``tt`` searches for it depends on the :ref:`launch mode <tt-config_modes>`."
" You can also pass the configuration file explicitly in the ``--cfg`` "
":ref:`option <tt-global-options>`."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"The ``tt`` configuration file is a YAML file with the following content:"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"tt:\n"
"  modules:\n"
"    directory: path/to/modules/dir\n"
"  app:\n"
"    instances_enabled: path/to/applications\n"
"    run_dir: path/to/run_dir\n"
"    log_dir: path/to/log_dir\n"
"    bin_dir: path/to/bin_dir\n"
"    inc_dir: path/to/inc_dir\n"
"    wal_dir: path/to/wal_dir\n"
"    vinyl_dir: path/to/vinyl_dir\n"
"    memtx_dir: path/to/memtx_dir\n"
"    log_maxsize: num (MB)\n"
"    log_maxage: num (days)\n"
"    log_maxbackups: num\n"
"    restart_on_failure: bool\n"
"  repo:\n"
"    rocks: path/to/rocks\n"
"    distfiles: path/to/install\n"
"  ee:\n"
"    credential_path: path/to/file\n"
"  templates:\n"
"    - path: path/to/app/templates1\n"
"    - path: path/to/app/templates2"
msgstr ""

msgid "modules section"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"``directory`` -- the directory where :doc:`external modules "
"<external_modules>` are stored."
msgstr ""

msgid "app section"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"``instances_enabled`` -- the directory where :ref:`instances <admin-"
"instance_file>` are stored."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"``run_dir``-- the directory for instance runtime artifacts, such as console "
"sockets or PID files. Default: ``var/run``."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"``log_dir`` -- the directory where log files are stored. Default: "
"``var/log``."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"``bin_dir`` -- the directory where binary files are stored. Default: "
"``bin``."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"``inc_dir`` -- the base directory for storing header files. They will be "
"placed in the ``include`` subdirectory inside the specified directory. "
"Default: ``include``."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"``wal_dir`` -- the directory where write-ahead log (``.xlog``) files are "
"stored. Default: ``var/lib``."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"``memtx_dir`` -- the directory where memtx stores snapshot (``.snap``) "
"files. Default: ``var/lib``."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"``vinyl_dir`` -- the directory where vinyl files or subdirectories are "
"stored. Default: ``var/lib``."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"In all directories specified in ``*_dir`` parameters, ``tt`` creates a "
"directory for each application and instance directories inside it. Names of "
"these directories match the names of applications and instances."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"``log_maxsize`` -- the maximum size of the log file before it gets rotated, "
"in megabytes. Default: 100."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"``log_maxage`` -- the maximum age of log files in days. The age of a log "
"file is defined by the timestamp encoded in its name. Default: not defined "
"(log files aren't deleted based on their age)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"A day is defined as exactly 24 hours. It may not exactly correspond to "
"calendar days due to daylight savings, leap seconds, and other time "
"adjustments."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"``log_maxbackups`` -- the maximum number of stored log files. Default: not "
"defined (log files aren't deleted based on their count)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"``restart_on_failure`` -- restart the instance on failure: ``true`` or "
"``false``. Default: ``false``."
msgstr ""

msgid "repo section"
msgstr ""

msgid "``rocks`` -- the directory where rocks files are stored."
msgstr ""

msgid "``distfiles`` -- the directory where installation files are stored."
msgstr ""

msgid "ee section"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"``credential_path`` -- a path to the file with credentials used for "
"downloading Tarantool Enterprise Edition."
msgstr ""

msgid "templates section"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"``path`` -- a path to application templates used for creating applications "
"with :ref:`tt create <tt-create>`. May be specified more than once."
msgstr ""

msgid "Launch modes"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"``tt`` launch mode defines its working directory and the way it searches for"
" the configuration file. There are three launch modes:"
msgstr ""

msgid "default"
msgstr ""

msgid "system"
msgstr ""

msgid "local"
msgstr ""

msgid "Default launch"
msgstr ""

msgid "**Argument**: none"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"**Configuration file**: searched from the current directory to the root. "
"Taken from ``/etc/tarantool`` if the file is not found."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"**Working directory**: The directory where the configuration file is found."
msgstr ""

msgid "System launch"
msgstr ""

msgid "**Argument**: ``--system`` or ``-S``"
msgstr ""

msgid "**Configuration file**: Taken from ``/etc/tarantool``."
msgstr ""

msgid "**Working directory**: Current directory."
msgstr ""

msgid "Local launch"
msgstr ""

msgid "**Argument**: ``--local=DIRECTORY`` or ``-L=DIRECTORY``"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"**Configuration file**: Searched from the specified directory to the root. "
"Taken from ``/etc/tarantool`` if the file is not found."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"**Working directory**: The specified directory. If ``tarantool`` or ``tt`` "
"executable files are found in the working directory, they will be used."
msgstr ""
